                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>The sleeper mounted radio controls provides the radio AM/FM band select, station seek
                                (up &#38; down), volume, power and alarm.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sleeper mounted control panel.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Operates OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of open condition, then repair. Replace sleeper mounted radio control.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>The radio control LCD panel with amber (backlight), and VOL button, SEEK/TUNE button,
                                BAND MODE button, SEL button with amber (LED), and PWR button with red (LED)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>LCD panel</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>Operates OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Replace defective radio control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>The sleeper mounted radio controls through seven circuits from the sleeper mounted
                                control panel connector (1323), at "B" pillar, and connector (1322), at the radio.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1323), at "B" pillar, and connector (1322), at the radio.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Operates OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connectors (1322) and (1323). Measure resistance of circuit ILL (8V)
                                through connector (1322) contact A to connector (1323) contact A and sleeper panel
                                connector contact A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1322) contact A to (1323) contact A</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit LCD D1 through connector (1322) contact C to connector
                                (1323) contact C and sleeper panel connector contact C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1322) contact C to (1323) contact C</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit LCD D0 through connector (1322) contact D to connector
                                (1323) contact D and sleeper panel connector contact D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1322) contact D to (1323) contact D</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit V D0 through connector (1322) contact E to connector
                                (1323) contact E and sleeper panel connector contact E.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1322) contact E to (1323) contact E</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit LCD CLK through connector (1322) contact F to connector
                                (1323) contact F and sleeper panel connector contact F.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1322) contact F to (1323) contact F</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit LCD DE through connector (1322) contact G to connector
                                (1323) contact G and sleeper panel connector contact G.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1322) contact G to (1323) contact G</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuit GND through connector (1322) contact H to connector
                                (1323) contact H and sleeper panel connector contact H.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1322) contact H to (1323) contact H</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection, then repair. Repair circuit or replace defective
                                cable.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnector connectors (1322) and (1323), the sleeper mounted radio controls and
                                circuits check good.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center"></entry>
                        <entry align="center"></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                    </row>
